<HL>
   Bennetton Family Sells
   62% of Financial Firm
   ----
   Special to The Wall Street Journal
</HL>
<DATE>
06/25/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A9D
</SO>
<CO>
   BNG
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   MILAN, Italy -- The Benetton family of Italy sold a 62%
stake in its financial-services group, In Capital S.p.A., to
Sviluppo Finanziaria, the investment bank of Franceso
Micheli's Finarte S.p.A. Terms weren't disclosed.
   The Benetton family holding, Edizione Holding S.p.A., will
retain a 26% stake in In Capital, and management will keep a
12% interest, Svilippo said.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Sviluppo said the new group after the acquisition will
control about 40 trillion lire ($32.54 billion) in
financial-services activities.
</TEXT>
